<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT * FROM lawyer</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>select * from lawyer</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>SELECT name, address FROM lawyer</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT name, address FROM client</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select lawyer.name, lawyer.address, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id</s>

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name, lawyer.address, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name, lawyer.address, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id</s>

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select lawyer.name, lawyer.address, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.name, case.case_name FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>select client.name, case.case_name from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>SELECT client.name, case.case_name FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>select case.case_name, hearing.hearing_date from case inner join hearing on case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT case.case_name, document.document_name FROM case INNER JOIN document ON case.case_id = document.case_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name AS lawyer_name, client.name AS client_name, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id INNER JOIN client ON client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select lawyer.name as lawyer_name, client.name as client_name, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id inner join client on client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name AS lawyer_name, client.name AS client_name, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id INNER JOIN client ON client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select lawyer.name as lawyer_name, client.name as client_name, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id inner join client on client.id = case.client_id</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>select lawyer.name as lawyer_name, client.name as client_name, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id inner join client on client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name AS lawyer_name, client.name AS client_name, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id INNER JOIN client ON client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select lawyer.name as lawyer_name, client.name as client_name, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id inner join client on client.id = case.client_id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name AS lawyer_name, client.name AS client_name, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id INNER JOIN client ON client.id = case.client_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select lawyer.name as lawyer_name, client.name as client_name, case.case_name from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id inner join client on client.id = case.client_id</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name AS lawyer_name, client.name AS client_name, case.case_name FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id INNER JOIN client ON client.id = case.client_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, hearing.hearing_date FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN hearing ON case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, hearing.hearing_date FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN hearing ON case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select client.name as client_name, hearing.hearing_date from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join hearing on case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select client.name as client_name, hearing.hearing_date from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join hearing on case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, hearing.hearing_date FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN hearing ON case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.name as client_name, hearing.hearing_date from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join hearing on case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select lawyer.name as lawyer_name, hearing.hearing_date from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id inner join hearing on case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.name AS lawyer_name, hearing.hearing_date FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id INNER JOIN hearing ON case.case_id = hearing.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.name as client_name, document.document_name from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join document on case.case_id = document.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, document.document_name FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN document ON case.case_id = document.case_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, document.document_name FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN document ON case.case_id = document.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.name as client_name, document.document_name from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join document on case.case_id = document.case_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, document.document_name FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN document ON case.case_id = document.case_id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.name as client_name, document.document_name from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join document on case.case_id = document.case_id</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select client.name as client_name, document.document_name from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id inner join document on case.case_id = document.case_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.name AS client_name, document.document_name FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id INNER JOIN document ON case.case_id = document.case_id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select lawyer.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id group by lawyer.id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>select lawyer.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id group by lawyer.id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select lawyer.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id group by lawyer.id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id GROUP BY lawyer.id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT lawyer.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id GROUP BY lawyer.id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select lawyer.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from lawyer inner join case on lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id group by lawyer.id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT lawyer.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id GROUP BY lawyer.id</s>

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT lawyer.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM lawyer INNER JOIN case ON lawyer.id = case.lawyer_id GROUP BY lawyer.id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id GROUP BY client.id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id group by client.id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id GROUP BY client.id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id group by client.id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>SELECT client.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id GROUP BY client.id</s>

CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>SELECT client.id, COUNT(case_id) AS total_cases FROM client INNER JOIN case ON client.id = case.client_id GROUP BY client.id</s>

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select client.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id group by client.id</s>

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))</t><s>select client.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id group by client.id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE document (document_id INT PRIMARY KEY, document_name STRING, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE hearing (hearing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, hearing_date DATE, case_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (case_id) REFERENCES case(case_id))

CREATE TABLE case (case_id INT PRIMARY KEY, case_name STRING, lawyer_id INT, client_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (lawyer_id) REFERENCES lawyer(id), FOREIGN KEY (client_id) REFERENCES client(id))

CREATE TABLE client (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)

CREATE TABLE lawyer (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name STRING, address STRING)</t><s>select client.id, count(case_id) as total_cases from client inner join case on client.id = case.client_id group by client.id</s>
